            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "4daa8789210c_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "df9d",
          "text": "Daniel: In 2006 after finishing my PhD I visited David Orr at Oberlin College and interviewed him about the role of design in the transition ahead. His answer to one of the questions was: “Before we can adequately answer the question what we might have to do to design a sustainable human presence on Earth and how we might go about doing it, we need to ask ourselves a much more difficult question: Why is humanity worth sustaining? Why are we worth it?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 7,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "4daa8789210c_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7c99",
          "text": "What do you think might be humanity’s role and saving grace? Why are we worth sustaining?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
